  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening justice and accountability for international and transnational crimes in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A total of 32 prosecutors from the Complex Casework Group within the  Directorate of Public Prosecutions, and 30 investigators and prosecutors from the Nigerian military.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities: training workshops, in-house mentoring sessions, high-level meetings, public symposia, and media engagements.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Outcome 1: Well-trained Nigerian civilian and military investigators and  prosecutors who have the knowledge and skills to investigate and  prosecute international crimes, transnational organised crimes and terrorism under Nigerian law. 
Outcome 2: Enhanced inter-agency collaboration between law  enforcement, military and prosecution agencies. 
Outcome 3: Well-informed citizenry through outreach activities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall goal of the project is to ensure that the Nigerian justice system is better equipped to investigate and prosecute international crimes genuinely and effectively in line with Nigeria&#x2019;s obligations under the Rome Statute.</narrative>
  </description>
